Throwables - a) Errors - b)Exceptions
Exceptions - a) Checked b) Unchecked 
Unchecked - a) Runtime


Checked Exception - 
If a checked exception could potentially occur in a method or a class and that exception is not handled, the code will not compile at all.

Unchecked Exception - 
Unchecked throwables include all errors and any runtime exceptions, which are not checked at compile time. Apps will likely not be able to recover at all from an unchecked throwable

Errors - 
1) IOError 2) VirtualMachineError


VirtualMachineError 
1) Internal Error 2) Unknown Error 3) Out of memory Error 4) Stack overflow error
